description.narrative:
1.	Daily access to safe water provided to 8,670 Households with a population of 43,350;
2.	Adequate sanitation provided to 225 most vulnerable Households with a population of 1800;
3.	Hygiene promotion activities targeting 43,350 including COVID 19 hygiene behaviour;
4.	Improved equitable access to basic and financial services, considering different needs based on gender and other diversity factors;
5.	Prevent and respond to sexual- and gender-based violence, child marriage and all forms of violence against children.

Contribution of the 3FM SR 2020 and 2021 COVID Campaign to ZRCS for COVID-19 intervention, and to the health care system in Zambia. Under the main focus of “Help the Helpers”,  the main strategy will be to support health care workers, Red Cross volunteers/staff, within the COVID-19 response under the protection, care and support e.g. IPC knowledge, PPEs; but also, PSS. Necessary tools will be provided to ensure good care and support such as medical Supplies & equipment, IPC and related training.
Besides prevention work will be built in to support the overall aim of decreasing morbidity and mortality due to COVID-19. This includes more prevention at a community level, better access to care and higher healthcare-seeking behavior (e.g. reducing barriers such as stigma, fears addressing PSS and RCCE); and better care at Health facilities. 
Overall support to National Society Development (NSD) is important for continuity/sustainability.  The National Society will implement the project around three (3) pillars, building on what has been set up and areas that capacity and expertise exists already;

